DURBAN - Armed robbers stole an undisclosed amount of cash and a laptop from Bargain Basket on Barnsley Road in Pietermaritzburg on Monday.Provincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said it was alleged that on January 3 at 3.45pm, armed men entered the business premises on Barnsley Road.She said the suspects held up the manager.“At gunpoint they took an undisclosed amount of cash, a laptop and fled the scene,” said Mbele.In a statement on Facebook on Monday, Bargain Basket said the store had fallen victim to an armed robbery.MORE ON THISPMB police officer undergoes emergency surgery after being shot by suspect in jewellery store robberyFour suspects armed with handguns rob Chatsworth sports bar and patrons of liquor, cellphones and cashCash-in-transit robbery suspect hands himself over to authorities“We would like to praise our staff members and the customers who got caught up in the situation for their calm response and swift action,” said the store.Bargain Basket said the female manager was treated for shock at a hospital.The store said it had arranged debriefing and counselling for all staff members yesterday.“We would also like to extend an invitation to any customer who was impacted by these events to contact us, so that we can also assist with counselling,”said the store.Bargain Basket added that this process would affect their operations.“We would like you to please be patient and kind when visiting,” said the store.THE MERCURY